  "rootNodeId": "lp-root",
  "lastModified": 1784814066402,
  "nodes": {
    "lp-root": {
      "id": "lp-root",
      "name": "IdeaM -- Launch Progress",
      "content": "<p><strong>Last updated:</strong> 2026-07-23</p><p></p><p><strong>Overall: 99% complete (179/180 tasks) — BETA LIVE</strong></p><pre><code>█████████████████████████████░</code></pre><p></p><p><strong>Bootstrap roadmap — you are here:</strong></p><pre><code>Phase 1  Establish Web Presence    ✅ done\nPhase 2  App Store Preparation     ✅ done  (TestFlight Build 3 live)\nPhase 3  Validate Before Scaling   ◀ YOU ARE HERE  (beta feedback)\nPhase 4  Launch &amp; Early Revenue    ○ next   (public launch + paid SKU)\nPhase 5  Scale When Revenue Allows ○ later</code></pre><p></p><p><strong>By category:</strong></p><p>Documents &amp; drafts:     100% <code>████████████████████████</code> 15/15</p><p>Code changes:            100% <code>████████████████████████</code> 53/53</p><p>Decision docs:          100% <code>████████████████████████</code> 5/5</p><p>Bug fixes:             100% <code>████████████████████████</code> 3/3</p><p>Awaiting your decisions: 0% <code>░░░░░░░░░░░░░░░░░░░░░░░░</code> 0/5</p><p>External / user-only:    50% <code>████████████░░░░░░░░░░░░</code> 6/12</p><p>Post-launch (deferred):   0% <code>░░░░░░░░░░░░░░░░░░░░░░░░</code> 0/10</p><p></p><p><strong>━━━ Shipped 2026-07-23 (cont.) — Pricing model, server-side AI cost meter, always-on verifier ━━━</strong></p><ul><li><p><strong>Pricing model set.</strong> Email, Social, and Your Voice are included in Professional — no new SKU, no add-on. They add no separate cost worth pricing; the free floor runs on-device or on the user's own key at $0 to us, and the paid path rides the existing first-month-free trial.</p></li><li><p><strong>Server-side AI cost meter — SHIPPED.</strong> A per-account, atomic, fail-closed usage meter guards every cloud AI call across all vendors (text, image, audio, voice). Free accounts get zero company AI; our key is reachable only by internal dev accounts today (the paid door stays OFF until subscription verification is wired). Retries are capped, and a permanent cost-guardrails test is now a release blocker.</p></li><li><p><strong>Always-on verifier — SHIPPED.</strong> A quiet, on-device safety net double-checks factual AI output (emails, posts, summaries, inbound) and flags-and-suggests — never silently rewrites. It costs nothing and never touches the usage meter. Messaging stays conservative and promise-free everywhere.</p></li></ul>\n<p><strong>━━━ Shipped 2026-07-23 — Email suite, Your Voice, Social export lineup ━━━</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li><p><strong>Professional Customization — opt-in framework SHIPPED.</strong> A new settings section with a master switch plus granular toggles turns on the professional email and social tools. Everything is OFF by default; IdeaM never touches a user's accounts on its own, and the consent screen honestly shows both the upside and the trade-offs.</p></li>\n<li><p><strong>Export Email — SHIPPED.</strong> Turn an outline (or a chapter) into a ready-to-send professional email, with four honest hand-off paths depending on what each destination actually supports.</p></li>\n<li><p><strong>Import Email — SHIPPED.</strong> Bring an email or a whole thread into an outline. Suspected junk is quarantined into a clearly labeled side branch instead of being deleted, so nothing is ever lost.</p></li>\n<li><p><strong>Your Voice — SHIPPED.</strong> Optional personal writing-style emulation: the wizards can write in the user's OWN voice. Strictly the user's own style, never impersonating anyone else.</p></li>\n<li><p><strong>Share to Social — full lineup SHIPPED.</strong> Seven one-stop social formats on a shared, extensible template: X, Instagram (caption + carousel), LinkedIn, Facebook, Threads, Bluesky, and YouTube (a full publish package plus Shorts). Hand-offs are honest — one-click compose only where the platform truly allows it (X, Threads, Bluesky), clean copy/paste elsewhere (LinkedIn, Facebook) — no fake buttons.</p></li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>━━━ Shipped 2026-07-22 — Digest rename, bulk outline delete, local-AI resilience + silent start, Summarize wizard ━━━</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li><p><strong>&quot;Digest&quot; rename — SHIPPED.</strong> The import/merge action button (formerly &quot;Synthesize&quot;) is now &quot;Digest&quot; — clearer, value-based naming that says what the button does: it digests your imported sources into your outline.</p></li>\n<li><p><strong>Bulk delete of multi-selected outlines — FIXED + SHIPPED.</strong> Right-clicking a multi-selection now deletes the whole batch at once, with a count label and a confirmation prompt, in both the outline list and the sidebar. Fixes a real bug where deleting a multi-selection silently did nothing.</p></li>\n<li><p><strong>Local-AI (Ollama) resilience — SHIPPED.</strong> For Local-mode users, the on-device AI engine now auto-starts after a reboot, and dead-end &quot;not available&quot; errors are replaced with a calm &quot;Start Local AI&quot; notice that offers an install link and cloud fallbacks. Cloud-only users are unaffected.</p></li>\n<li><p><strong>Headless local-AI start — SHIPPED.</strong> The local engine now starts silently in the background — no launch window pops up in the user&#39;s face.</p></li>\n<li><p><strong>Summarize Outline wizard — SHIPPED.</strong> One click distills an outline into a gist, saved as a new outline by default (the original is preserved) or written in place with confirmation.</p></li>\n<li><p><strong>Test suite health — DONE.</strong> Added automated tests covering the above and fixed a stale-selector suite so &quot;TEST EVERYTHING&quot; passes green.</p></li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>━━━ Shipped 2026-07-08 — Generate Video (desktop v1) ━━━</strong></p>\n<ul><li><p><strong>Generate Video — SHIPPED (desktop v1).</strong> Turn a chapter (a selected node plus its descendants) into a finished narrated slideshow video, exported as an MP4 — entirely inside the desktop app. Ships with professionally designed slides, a Style step for branding (logo, accent color, light/dark theme, and a narrator voice unified with the podcast voices), Pro-tier gating, and full documentation. Committed, pushed, and iOS-synced. <em>Future v1.1:</em> web + iOS video rendering will run through a server-side render service — a future enhancement, NOT a launch blocker.</p></li></ul>\n<p><strong>━━━ Shipped 2026-07-03 — TestFlight refresh + AI resilience + data-safety fix + SecondBrainWare LLC filed ━━━</strong></p>\n<ul><li><p><strong>TestFlight Build 3 uploaded — beta channel back online.</strong> The two prior TestFlight builds had aged out (Apple’s 90-day expiry), so IdeaM had stopped launching on Howard’s devices and Kathy’s. A fresh signed build (v1.0 build 3) was built and pushed from the command line. Internal devices get it immediately once Apple finishes processing; Kathy (external) after a one-time Apple beta review.</p></li><li><p><strong>Apple hands-off upload pipeline established.</strong> Accepted Apple’s updated developer license (which had silently locked Certificates + App Store Connect), and generated an App Store Connect API key so all future TestFlight uploads happen from the command line with no Xcode GUI step.</p></li><li><p><strong>AI resilience extended beyond Help.</strong> Podcast script generation now falls back to on-device Gemma if the cloud AI is down or rate-limited, matching the Help chat. OpenRouter wired in as a dormant secondary-cloud backup provider (activates the moment a key is added; zero behavior change until then).</p></li><li><p><strong>DATA-SAFETY FIX: an outline could vanish from the sidebar over one malformed bullet.</strong> The load-time validity check required every node to carry a string formatting prefix; a single missing/bad prefix silently dropped the WHOLE outline from the list. The Bootstrap Plan hit this and disappeared. Fixed systemically — a bad/missing prefix now auto-heals to blank on load instead of hiding the outline — protecting every outline. Bootstrap Plan restored to the sidebar (verified in-app).</p></li><li><p><strong>Housekeeping.</strong> Confirmed Google Cloud billing is clean (the intermittent dunning flag is resolved). Consolidated duplicate Planning and MCP outlines plus a blank template down to one clean canonical copy each (duplicates archived, not deleted). Branding relationship locked: SecondBrainWare = the company, IdeaM = the app.</p></li><li><p><strong>Business formed: SecondBrainWare LLC filed with the WA Secretary of State ($200, standard).</strong> Certificate of Formation with Initial Report submitted and paid; status Review Ready, awaiting state approval + UBI number (~5 business days). Registered agent = Howard (home address). Next biz-setup steps after approval: free EIN (federal tax ID) → business bank account → Stripe. This clears the biggest non-Apple launch gate; payment SKU + production switch + real-device test still ahead.</p></li></ul><p></p><p><strong>━━━ Shipped 2026-07-02 — iOS App Store gates + UI polish ━━━</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li><p><strong>All six remaining P0 iOS App Store code gates — SHIPPED.</strong> (1) iOS microphone / speech usage-description strings added so Apple no longer auto-rejects. (2) iOS paid upgrades hidden — Apple in-app purchase isn&#39;t wired, so iOS now shows only the free bring-your-own-key path; web and Mac are unchanged and still show paid tiers. (3) Real in-app Account Deletion — deletes the Clerk account, server-side records, and local data behind a confirm dialog (was the single biggest App Store rejection risk). (4) 44px touch targets across all toolbars, the format menu, row chevrons, and the mobile sidebar button. (5) HIG polish batch: Light / Dark / Auto theme selector (the app is no longer locked to dark), pinch-zoom re-enabled, iOS soft-keyboard handling, tiny text bumped up. (6) Bug fixed — Cmd+E / Cmd+Shift+E (Expand All / Collapse All) keyboard shortcuts now actually fire (the toolbar buttons already worked). Two residuals fold into the existing &quot;Real-device test pass&quot; user item and are NOT new gates: Account Deletion needs a live sign-in with real Clerk keys to test the full round-trip, and pinch-zoom + keyboard-scroll only fire on a real touch device (both verified correct in code).</p></li>\n<li><p><strong>Left-sidebar visual-hierarchy redesign — SHIPPED.</strong> The outline sidebar is reorganized into labeled clusters with dividers and accent icons so the eye lands on the right group instantly instead of scanning a flat list.</p></li>\n<li><p><strong>Both toolbars given the matching treatment — SHIPPED.</strong> The main and secondary toolbars now share the same visual-hierarchy language as the sidebar for a consistent, professional feel.</p></li>\n<li><p><strong>Responsive toolbar overflow &quot;More&quot; menu — SHIPPED.</strong> On narrow windows the toolbar collapses lower-priority actions into a &quot;More&quot; menu so nothing gets cut off or crowded.</p></li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>━━━ Shipped 2026-06-25 → 2026-06-30 — BETA LIVE ━━━</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li><p><strong>MILESTONE: First real beta user fully onboarded end-to-end (Kathy, Howard&#39;s wife).</strong> The full signup chain — application form on the marketing site → admin approval in /admin/applicants → personal welcome email → Clerk account creation → into the app — was validated with a real human, not a test fixture. This was THE last gating item between &quot;site exists&quot; and &quot;users can actually sign up and use IdeaM.&quot; Beta is now genuinely open.</p></li>\n<li><p><strong>Clerk auth wired end-to-end — SHIPPED.</strong> Publishable + secret keys live in Vercel. Middleware bug that was crashing every protected route (auth() returning a promise that wasn&#39;t awaited) fixed. ClerkProvider initialization race resolved so protected pages no longer flash a login wall before knowing the user&#39;s status. The waiting page now shows the signed-in user&#39;s email so they know which account is being checked. Allowlist gate checks ALL of a Clerk user&#39;s linked email addresses (primary + secondaries), not just the primary, so users who applied with one address and signed up with another don&#39;t get bounced. The dev/test Clerk environment is what&#39;s live in production today; the dev→prod environment swap is deferred (see Up next).</p></li>\n<li><p><strong>Upstash KV (production storage) provisioned + connected — SHIPPED.</strong> A real persistent key-value store now sits behind the applicant, bug, and feedback storage layers. Previously the production site was silently dropping every write (the no-op stub mode that the dual-mode storage adapter falls back to when no KV is configured). All three flows now actually persist. Verified by the Kathy signup loop — her application written, retrieved, approved, and email sent.</p></li>\n<li><p><strong>In-app bug reporting — NEW FEATURE shipped.</strong> Users can now report bugs without leaving IdeaM. Report Issue button in the toolbar plus a Help-menu entry open a dialog with: description (min 3 chars), severity selector, optional screenshot attach, platform auto-detected and shown as a clean human label (Mac Desktop / iOS / Web / Windows / Linux). Submissions go to a new admin page at /admin/bugs with status filtering, internal-only progress notes only Howard sees, and email notifications to howard@2ndbrainware.com on every new report. Toast confirmation on submit, polished error handling, fully responsive. Documented in all four mandatory places.</p></li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>━━━ Shipped 2026-06-11 ━━━</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li><p><strong>Multimedia AI (Phase 1) — SHIPPED.</strong> Two related capabilities ship together: (a) <em>Capture from image</em> — pick or take a photo of a whiteboard, mind map, sticky-note board, or slide screenshot, and Gemini extracts a hierarchical outline into a three-panel preview (source thumbnail / editable proposed tree / where it lands); Apply appends the new nodes as children of the selected node with an auto-snapshot first and a single Cmd+Z step, with &quot;Save as new outline&quot; as an opt-in via the derivative flow. iOS/Android adds a native &quot;Take photo&quot; button via the HTML capture attribute. (b) <em>Share as YouTube package</em> — turn a chapter (selected node + descendants) into a complete YouTube content package with 8 outputs in 8 editable tabs: voiceover script with shot markers, chapter list, 200-300 word description, 5 title variants, 15-20 SEO tags, thumbnail concept, B-roll prompts (Runway / MagicLight / Sora), and a screen-recording shot list. Export as markdown or save as a new derivative outline. Both features count as one generation each against the monthly cap. New server actions, new feature keys in the AI usage gate, three new files + edits to seven existing files. Documented in all five mandatory places. Marketing outline updated — previously listed as &quot;planned v1.1&quot;, now shipping in v1.</p></li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>━━━ Shipped 2026-06-10 ━━━</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li><p><strong>Derivative outlines (third protective layer) — SHIPPED.</strong> Every content-altering AI transform (Transform Outline with AI, Reformat with AI, Refresh from Web) now defaults to &quot;Save as new outline&quot; — the result becomes a NEW outline nested under the original, and the original is NOT modified. The user can still opt in to &quot;Replace this outline&quot;, in which case the auto-snapshot from Layer 2 still fires and Cmd+Z still undoes. Translate keeps in-place as its default (translation is content-preserving per language and the user already chose the target language) but offers derivative as opt-in. Derivative labels auto-suggest from the user&apos;s prompt (&quot;rewrite for middle schoolers&quot; → &quot;Middle School Version&quot;). Derivatives nest in the sidebar with a small purple fork badge. A subtle &quot;Derived from [Parent]&quot; banner appears at the top of derivative outlines with an &quot;Open original&quot; button. Multi-level derivation supported. Orphan derivatives (parent deleted) render at top-level with a muted hint. Two new optional fields on the Outline interface — derivedFromOutlineId and derivationLabel — both backward-compatible. Documented in all 4 places + Decisions Log entry. TS baseline preserved. Playwright probe confirmed the default behavior and label auto-suggestion.</p></li>\n<li><p><strong>Backup &amp; Restore + Auto-snapshots before AI transforms — SHIPPED.</strong> Second protective layer in the outline-data-protection model (the first being unified Cmd+Z). Shield button in the outline toolbar opens a Backup / Restore dialog: Backup tab takes an optional label and writes a full disk snapshot; Restore tab lists every snapshot for the current outline (newest first) with Preview / Restore / Delete per row. Every AI transform — Reformat, Translate, Transform Outline, Refresh from Web — auto-snapshots the outline before applying, labeled &quot;auto: before [transform name]&quot;. Restore action auto-saves the current state first as &quot;auto: before restore&quot; so the user can roll back. Settings &gt; Outline backups has both toggles (default ON) plus a Show backups folder button. Retention: 20 newest snapshots per outline, oldest deleted automatically. Snapshots live at [outlines folder] / .backups / [outline-name]. Documented in all 4 places + Decisions Log entry.</p></li>\n<li><p><strong>Beta feedback form + 1-year Pro reward — SHIPPED.</strong> New page at /feedback gathers structured beta feedback (NPS, overall stars, a row per killer feature pulled verbatim from the marketing site, open-ended best/wish prompts, workflow context, optional testimonial consent with attribution + photo + 30-second video, friction question, follow-up consent). Submitting unlocks 1 year of Pro features at no charge (BYOK on API) and emails Howard a structured summary. Video testimonials flip a Founding User badge on the account. Daily Vercel cron at /api/cron/feedback-reminder sends a one-shot reminder ~14 days after beta approval. Admin browsing at /admin/feedback (search, filter chips, CSV export). Welcome email extended to telegraph the ask in abstract terms. Documented in all 4 places + Decisions Log entry. Verified end-to-end via Playwright probe (10/10 passing).</p></li>\n\n<li><p><strong>Beta-applicant approval flow — SHIPPED.</strong> Replaces the prior \"naked /app link\" home-page bypass with a full applicant lifecycle. New users apply at /signup (name + email + optional reason). Howard reviews each application in /admin/applicants and clicks Approve. Approval flips the record, adds the email to the dynamic allowlist with no redeploy, and sends a personal \"you're in\" email from howard@2ndbrainware.com (Reply-To Howard so users can write back). The /app subtree is now wrapped in AppGate, which redirects unapproved users to a friendly /waiting page. Defense in depth: Clerk webhook re-checks via async allowlist union (env var + applicant store). Storage extends the existing file-based JSON pattern at .idiampro/applicants.json — zero new dependencies. Documented in all 4 places and verified end-to-end via Playwright (9/9 passing).</p></li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>━━━ Shipped 2026-06-05 / 2026-06-06 ━━━</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li><p><strong>macOS desktop auto-updater — SHIPPED AT LAUNCH (2026-06-06).</strong> <code>electron-updater</code> integrated end-to-end. Silent check 8 seconds after launch + re-check every 4 hours. Updates download in the background; non-intrusive top-of-shell banner (<em>\"Update ready. Version X.Y.Z is ready. Restart to apply.\"</em>) surfaces with Restart now / Later (24h snooze) buttons. Help menu &gt; \"Check for Updates…\" allows manual check with friendly toast feedback. Skipped in dev mode. Feed URL configured against the marketing site at <code>2ndbrainware.com/updates/mac/latest.yml</code> (primary domain; secondbrainware.com becomes redirect-only). Code-signing / Apple Developer cert / Vercel hosting upload remain on Howard's external punch list — the code-side integration ships now, the feed turns on the moment those externals are wired. Moved from Post-launch / deferred to Shipped at launch.</p></li>\n<li><p><strong>Reformat with AI — NEW AI SURFACE.</strong> Users describe a format change in plain language; AI applies with preview-and-approve cycle. Reachable from Smart Tools, right-click, bubble menu (first position with \"Most Powerful\" badge), Command Palette. Tier-gated. Six example chips to seed the input. Reuses transform-engine pattern from LIVE BOOKS / Translate.</p></li>\n<li><p><strong>Discovery Hints system + Professional mode — NEW UX FRAMEWORK.</strong> Persistent \"Did You Know?\" cards for new users on five v1 triggers (Reformat, Smart Tools menu, cross-links, Import/Export buttons, BYOK). Two-tier dismissal: \"Got it\" alone = soft (re-fires next time); checkbox + Got it = permanent. Professional mode toggle in Settings suppresses all hints; toggling off re-enables anything not permanently dismissed. Storage migration handles existing dismissed-hint data. Foundation reusable for future hints app-wide.</p></li>\n<li><p><strong>Outline search redesigned — view-shaper + persistent state + AND-chain.</strong> Searching now reshapes the outline itself (matches' ancestors expanded, descendants collapsed, non-matching subtrees hidden) and the new state persists after closing the search bar. New \"Search only open nodes\" funnel toggle restricts the next search to currently-visible nodes — successive searches become a logical AND chain. Howard's design.</p></li>\n<li><p><strong>Toolbar consolidation: -3 buttons.</strong> Quick Capture merged into Brain menu (cognitive flow: enter → capture → save → explore). Expand All and Collapse All merged into single bidirectional-chevron dropdown (\"Show or hide all nodes\"). Refresh from Web relocated from Smart Tools to Import menu. Import as Chapter dead code + 5 orphan component files deleted.</p></li>\n<li><p><strong>Responsive toolbar with overflow-menu pattern.</strong> Three breakpoints (phone &lt; 640px, tablet 640-1024px, desktop ≥ 1024px). Sidebar toggle leftmost anchor, account avatar rightmost anchor. Tier 1 always inline (Ask AI, basic action row, Search). Tier 2 (Import, Export, Focus, Brain menu, Smart Tools, Show-or-hide, Share, Command Palette) inline on tablet+. Tier 3 (Settings, Help, Wrench) inline on desktop only. Overflow popover catches the rest.</p></li>\n<li><p><strong>Recursive Expand All / Collapse All — fixed bug.</strong> The original Expand All only went one level. Now both commands recurse through every descendant. Per-node state preserved on casual chevron clicks (reopening shows what was there); explicit commands fully reset.</p></li>\n<li><p><strong>Value-based renames across the app.</strong> \"AI Features\" → \"Smart Tools\", \"Tell AI…\" → \"Quick Command\", \"Knowledge Chat\" → \"Ask Your Outlines\", \"LIVE BOOKS\" → \"Refresh from Web\". Codified value-based naming as a permanent rule in user-level CLAUDE.md. Internal code identifiers unchanged.</p></li>\n<li><p><strong>Tech stack canonicalization across 5 outlines.</strong> Howard's plain-English explanation (\"no Python, TypeScript everywhere, Electron for desktop, Capacitor for iOS, Next.js for web\") canonicalized as a new \"Technology Stack & Platform Strategy\" chapter in How It Works, with strategic-value mirrors in BizDev (capital-efficiency lever), Killer Features (cross-platform parity from day one), Planning (strategic tech choice), and Bootstrap Plan (operational note).</p></li>\n<li><p><strong>Paste handler — text-fidelity pivot.</strong> Howard reversed direction from markdown-on-paste to a simpler text-fidelity path. Plain-text pastes (including from macOS Terminal's clipboard with its cosmetic styled-span HTML) now preserve the source verbatim — line breaks stay line breaks, no doubled vertical spacing. Markdown markers appear as literal characters. Rich-HTML pastes (real email/web) still use the existing preservation path.</p></li>\n<li><p><strong>Operating procedures hardened.</strong> Saved durable rules for Playwright-with-focus-management, delegate-test-scripts-to-subagents, surface-cleaner-approaches-immediately, auto-publish-after-substantial-work, canonical publish procedure (TypeScript check → dev-log scan → staged commit → push → cap sync → Launch Progress bump → outline dual-sync → environment verify → terminal refocus). Both user-level CLAUDE.md and project memory updated.</p></li>\n</ul>\n<p></p>\n<p><strong>━━━ Shipped 2026-06-04 ━━━</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li><p><strong>#3 LIVE BOOKS live-refresh test — DONE (medium follow-up #57).</strong> New Playwright test at tests/livebooks-live-refresh-test.js covers the AI refresh round-trip + post-refresh per-node diff cards. Two-prong mock strategy keeps the test deterministic. Test passes 4/4.</p></li>\n<li><p><strong>#4 Language translation — DONE.</strong> Existing translate dialog (paused on 2026-05-28) re-mounted in the app and wired into the Smart Tools menu + Command Palette. Tier-enforcement gate (#33) integrated. Languages re-ordered for globally-distributed-teams positioning (Chinese-Simplified, Portuguese-Brazilian, Spanish, French, Japanese, Korean, German, Italian, Hindi up top). Mobile-responsive dialog with stacked diff cards.</p></li>\n<li><p><strong>#5 Launch metrics dashboard — DONE.</strong> New /admin/metrics page with seven launch-week vitals (signups, activation, D1/D7 retention, free-to-paid conversion, AI runs in last 24h, MRR). Big-number cards with trend arrows. Admin-gated via browser-storage flag for v1; real admin role wires in with Clerk. Demo data labelled clearly; the data layer is structured so each metric wires to real telemetry one function at a time post-launch.</p></li>\n<li><p><strong>iOS stress-test exit affordance — DONE.</strong> Howard reported the /stress-test page had no way back to the homepage on iPhone after a test run. Added a sticky header at the top with a Back-to-IdeaM link + home icon. Stays visible while scrolling so the way out is always one tap away.</p></li>\n<li><p><strong>YouTube import silent-failure fix — DONE.</strong> Howard reported pasting a YouTube URL into Research & Import on iPhone, clicking Synthesize, and the dialog closing with no result and no error. Root cause: when AI data consent hadn't been granted, the parent handler silently returned, dialog interpreted as success and closed, consent prompt opened behind it (easy to miss on iOS). Fix: throw a tagged AI_CONSENT_REQUIRED error that the dialog catches and shows inline. Regression test at tests/youtube-import-test.js.</p></li>\n<li><p><strong>I/O toolbar buttons — DONE.</strong> Two new prominent toolbar buttons next to the Wrench: Import (BookDown icon — Research & Import, Import Outline, Restore All Outlines, Link to Outline…) and Export (BookUp icon — Share Subtree as…, Export Current Outline, Backup All Outlines). Wrench slimmed to just Refresh User Guide. Share Subtree still also lives in the per-node right-click menu.</p></li>\n<li><p><strong>Value-based naming pass — DONE.</strong> User-facing labels renamed to describe what features do, not how: \"AI Features\" → \"Smart Tools\", \"Tell AI…\" → \"Quick Command\", \"Knowledge Chat\" → \"Ask Your Outlines\", \"LIVE BOOKS\" → \"Refresh from Web\". Internal code identifiers unchanged. Codified as a permanent rule in the user-level CLAUDE.md so it carries to every future project.</p></li>\n<li><p><strong>Cross-outline link nodes — DONE (Phase 1 + Phase 2 both).</strong> New outline-link node type lets a user link one outline to another. Create via \"Link to Outline…\" in the Import dropdown or via right-click \"Insert Link to Outline…\". Click navigates to the linked outline. Deleted-target shows a muted style + toast. Phase 2: linked outlines appear INDENTED beneath their parent in the sidebar — chevron to expand/collapse, persisted per-outline across sessions. Multi-parent supported (B appears under both A and C if both link to it). Loop detection renders the second occurrence as a muted leaf with \"↻ Already shown above\". Phase 3 (AI features traversing links) deferred post-launch.</p></li>\n<li><p><strong>Operating procedures hardened.</strong> Saved durable cross-session rules for: warning before sustained CPU tasks (DO NOT CLOSE LID), verifying the dev environment is up before signing off, delegating product decisions with mandatory Decisions Log documentation, briefing subagents to forbid background tasks, value-based naming as a permanent principle. Created user-level CLAUDE.md so these rules carry to every future project.</p></li>\n<li><p><strong>TEST EVERYTHING 2026-06-04: 56/56 still green at start of day.</strong> Today's new tests (livebooks-live-refresh, translate, cross-link, sidebar-nesting, import-export-toolbar, youtube-import) parse-validated but pending full run in next verification cycle.</p></li>\n</ul>\n<p></p>\n<p><strong>Shipped 2026-05-17:</strong></p><ul><li><p><strong>Auth Phase 1 — DONE &amp; verified.</strong> Tier model + env-gated Clerk auth layer; dormant until keys are set.</p></li><li><p><strong>Auth Phase 2 — DONE.</strong> Billing scaffolding: env-gated Stripe + RevenueCat, dormant until keys. (Phase 3 = tier enforcement #33 still pending.)</p></li><li><p><strong>LIVE BOOKS — BUILT &amp; shipped.</strong> Generalized transform engine; documented in all 4 places; core surface runtime-proven by a new automated test (dialog/scope/preview/auto-apply-off/merge-overwrite all pass). Residual: live AI refresh round-trip + post-refresh diff cards not yet automation-covered (medium follow-up #57).</p></li><li><p><strong>Language translation (#52) de-risked</strong> — LIVE BOOKS shipped the shared transform engine it plugs into.</p></li></ul><p><strong>Gemini 3.5 Flash switch (#49) — DONE.</strong> Google I/O 2026 (2026-05-19) shipped Gemini 3.5 Flash, not a &quot;Gemini 4&quot;. The app-wide default now points at gemini-3.5-flash; 2.5 Flash stays registered as a one-line rollback. Soft launch-copy variant finalized in docs/launch/gemini-3.5-flash.md; the BYOK setup guide now notes Google&#39;s ~55-day free-tier data retention. Remaining: publish marketing copy + deploy.</p><p><strong>Infra:</strong> project relocated out of iCloud to ~/Developer/IdeaM (machine-load problem permanently resolved); git auth moved to macOS Keychain.</p><p><strong>TEST EVERYTHING 2026-05-17: 38/38 on clean runs</strong> (electron 8/8, gemma4 6/6, mcp 24/24); relocated repo validated healthy.</p><p></p><p><strong>Shipped 2026-06-01 → 2026-06-03:</strong></p><ul><li><p><strong>Voice command UI hard pullback (2026-06-01).</strong> Typed natural-language input is now the default; voice infrastructure preserved on disk but no longer reachable from the UI. Future voice surface will be dictation/accessibility only, never command/control. (Underlying commits c56c17b + dc1bc42.)</p></li><li><p><strong>Undo/redo regression fixed (2026-06-02).</strong> Three layered fixes — empty-input focus fall-through, pop-until-visible-change, and a suppressRedoClear window — restored expected behavior. Robustness suite went from 3/4 to 4/4. (Commit 810cebb.)</p></li><li><p><strong>Ollama &quot;installed-but-not-running&quot; UX (2026-06-03).</strong> Settings and Bulk Research dialogs now differentiate the installed-but-not-running state from not-installed, with new IPC handlers and a Start Ollama button. (Commit c7c7ffa.)</p></li><li><p><strong>TEST EVERYTHING 2026-06-03: 56/56 all green</strong> across 7 suites.</p></li></ul>",
      "type": "root",
